.TH "devm_lcd_device_register" 9 "devm_lcd_device_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_lcd_device_register \- resource managed lcd_device_register()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct lcd_device *" devm_lcd_device_register
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct device *parent "  ","
.BI "void *devdata "  ","
.BI "struct lcd_ops *ops "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the device to register
.IP "name" 12
the name of the device
.IP "parent" 12
a pointer to the parent device
.IP "devdata" 12
an optional pointer to be stored for private driver use
.IP "ops" 12
the lcd operations structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fIreturn\fP a struct lcd on success, or an ERR_PTR on error

Managed \fBlcd_device_register\fP. The lcd_device returned from this function
are automatically freed on driver detach. See \fBlcd_device_register\fP
for more information.
